Now I understand. From Channel.kt line 555-560:

```kotlin
public inline fun <T> ChannelResult<T>.onClosed(action: (exception: Throwable?) -> Unit): ChannelResult<T> {
    contract {
        callsInPlace(action, InvocationKind.AT_MOST_ONCE)
    }
    if (holder is ChannelResult.Closed) action(exceptionOrNull())
    return this
}
```

The `onClosed` block receives `exception: Throwable?` - if the channel was closed with an exception, it will receive that exception. The current `timeoutInternal` code doesn't check this exception at all.

The fix is simple: we need to add `it?.let { throw it }` inside the `onClosed` block, similar to how `onFailure` is handled in other operators.

The fix should be:

```kotlin
.onClosed {
    it?.let { throw it }  // Re-throw exception if present
    return@onReceiveCatching false
}
```

